OL,5, Network Rail has been fined #6.7m after
OL,6, admitting a series of failings which   
OL,7, led to the deaths of three people in a 
OL,8, train crash near Stonehaven.           
OL,10,FThe Aberdeen to Glasgow service        
OL,11,Fderailed at Carmont after hitting a    
OL,12,Flandslide following heavy rain.        
OL,14,FNetwork Rail pleaded guilty to a number
OL,15,Fof maintenance and inspection failures 
OL,16,Fbefore the crash in August 2020.       
OL,18,FIt also admitted failing to warn the   
OL,19,Fdriver that part of the track was      
OL,20,Funsafe or tell him to reduce his speed.
